<p><b>Is Carnegie Learning by Carnegie Mellon?</b> Carnegie Learning history was founded in 1988 as a research project at Carnegie Mellon University by Dr. Steven Ritter, William S. Hadley, John R. Anderson, and Kenneth Koedinger, researchers in cognitive science, computer science, and education.</p>
